<paragraph id="8B916F75FF82FFB2799541A2FDB6FAA5" blockId="16.[151,1437,151,1367]" pageId="16" pageNumber="477">
<emphasis id="B95AB367FF82FFB2799541A2FE14FB51" bold="true" box="[199,388,1162,1187]" pageId="16" pageNumber="477">Similar species:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C2E14F6FF82FFB278DE41A3FCB1FB51" authority="Frey, 1958" authorityName="Frey" authorityYear="1958" box="[396,801,1162,1187]" class="Insecta" family="Chamaemyiidae" genus="Melanochthiphila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="477" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aenea">
<emphasis id="B95AB367FF82FFB278DE41A3FD0FFB50" box="[396,671,1163,1187]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="477">Melanochthiphila aenea</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFBF1284FF82FFB27BF541A3FCB1FB51" author="Frey" box="[679,801,1162,1187]" pageId="16" pageNumber="477" refString="Frey, R. (1958) Zur Kenntnis der Diptera Brachycera p. p. der Kapverdischen Inseln. Commentationes Biologicae, 18, 1 - 61." type="journal article" year="1958">Frey, 1958</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was described from the 
<collectingCountry id="F3392FE5FF82FFB27D6941A3FB2EFB51" box="[1083,1214,1162,1187]" name="Cape Verde" pageId="16" pageNumber="477">
<collectingRegion id="49EAA197FF82FFB27D6941A3FBE5FB51" box="[1083,1141,1163,1187]" country="South Africa" name="Western Cape" pageId="16" pageNumber="477">Cape</collectingRegion>
Verde
</collectingCountry>
Islands where nine specimens were collected by H. Lindberg on a sandy costal area (
<bibRefCitation id="EFBF1284FF82FFB27A244187FC7EFB35" author="Frey" box="[886,1006,1198,1223]" pageId="16" pageNumber="477" refString="Frey, R. (1958) Zur Kenntnis der Diptera Brachycera p. p. der Kapverdischen Inseln. Commentationes Biologicae, 18, 1 - 61." type="journal article" year="1958">Frey 1958</bibRefCitation>
). I found another undescribed species, represented by only one female specimen, in a sandy area at altitude inland in 
<collectingCountry id="F3392FE5FF82FFB27D4C41FBFB13FB18" box="[1054,1155,1235,1258]" name="Morocco" pageId="16" pageNumber="477">Morocco</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFBF1284FF82FFB27DC641FAFAB5FB19" author="Ebejer" box="[1172,1317,1234,1259]" pageId="16" pageNumber="477" refString="Ebejer, M. J. (2016) The first record of the genus Melanochthiphila Frey (Diptera: Chamaemyiidae) from the Palaearctic, and data on other Chamaemyiidae from Morocco. Studia dipterologica, 22 (1), 111 - 120. [2015]" type="journal article" year="2016">Ebejer 2016</bibRefCitation>
). The new species differs from both of these in having a longer first flagellomere and much longer setae on the head and thorax, the whole body more lustrous and the femora entirely black. It also differs significantly from 
<taxonomicName id="4C2E14F6FF82FFB27DAB4033FA0BFAC0" baseAuthorityName="Frey" baseAuthorityYear="1958" box="[1273,1435,1307,1330]" class="Insecta" family="Chamaemyiidae" genus="Melanochthiphila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="477" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigroaenea">
<emphasis id="B95AB367FF82FFB27DAB4033FA0BFAC0" box="[1273,1435,1307,1330]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="477">M. nigroaenea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in details of the male postabdomen.
</paragraph>
